message.content: cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves reasoning and knowledge representation, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The statistical features used in the paper are collected from high-frequency words, which is a form of text mining and falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper analyzes the performance gaps between different feature extraction methods, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
